DAT
id=qid::label=str::text=lstr::
7960::$$$message_0077_0000_0000$$$::I ride the bus from school for twenty minutes.[lr]::
7961::$$$message_0077_0000_0001$$$::I arrive at Shinto, the neighboring town across the bridge.::
7962::$$$message_0077_0001_0000$$$::"Oh, it's not even five yet. I still have some time."[lr]::
7963::$$$message_0077_0001_0001$$$::There aren't many part time jobs in the residential area of Miyama, but there are plenty in Shinto since it's a developing area.[lr]::
7964::$$$message_0077_0001_0002$$$::Our school allows students to hold part-time jobs, so I take on simple jobs.::
7965::$$$message_0077_0002_0000$$$::I prefer my jobs to be physical, and the tougher and shorter they are, the better.[lr]::
7966::$$$message_0077_0002_0001$$$::I get paid all while training my body, so it's like killing two birds with one stone.::
7967::$$$message_0077_0003_0000$$$::Today, I'll work from five to eight o'clock for a simple loading job.[lr]::
7968::$$$message_0077_0003_0001$$$::It may just be three hours of work, but it feels more like six hours, since they make you work without a minute's rest.::
7969::$$$message_0077_0004_0000$$$::Which means I need to rest when I have the opportunity, even if it's just for ten minutes.[lr]::
7970::$$$message_0077_0004_0001$$$::Walking around aimlessly would be a waste of energy, so I decide to rest at a park until it's time.::
7971::$$$message_0077_0005_0000$$$::This park is nestled between buildings, and it's like a giant plaza full of trees and shrubbery.                                                                 [lr]::
7972::$$$message_0077_0005_0001$$$::A park should typically be filled with families and couples during weekends and holidays, but this one is deserted at this hour.[lr]::
7973::$$$message_0077_0005_0002$$$::In fairness, this place is always desolate, no matter the day or time.::
7974::$$$message_0077_0006_0000$$$::"This place is the same as always."[lr]::
7975::$$$message_0077_0006_0001$$$::I sigh in exasperation.[lr]::
7976::$$$message_0077_0006_0002$$$::The area is unkept, and it's really pretty ugly compared to other places that are properly landscaped and maintained.[lr]::
7977::$$$message_0077_0006_0003$$$::As if the desolate location had set the mood, the wind itself blows cold and harsh.[lr]::
7978::$$$message_0077_0006_0004$$$::This place is the remnant of the great catastrophe that happened ten years ago; it's the very place where I was saved from the brink of death.::
7979::$$$message_0077_0007_0000$$$::"Why don't they seed some grass here or something? It's a shame to keep it like this." [lr]::
7980::$$$message_0077_0007_0001$$$::The area is quite large, so if they leveled it, there'd be plenty of space to work on the park.[lr]::
7981::$$$message_0077_0007_0002$$$::I sit down on a bench as I think.::
7982::$$$message_0077_0008_0000$$$::[font italic=true]...[font italic=false][lr]::
7983::$$$message_0077_0008_0001$$$::With nothing else to do, I stare out over the burned area to pass the time.[lr]::
7984::$$$message_0077_0008_0002$$$::I don't remember anything that happened here.[lr]::
7985::$$$message_0077_0008_0003$$$::The only thing I remember is that it was hot, and I couldn't breathe.[lr]::
7986::$$$message_0077_0008_0004$$$::...And that some people died trying to save others.::
7987::$$$message_0077_0009_0000$$$::"I wonder why that happened."[lr]::
7988::$$$message_0077_0009_0001$$$::One adult here died because they were trying to save a child from a burning house.[lr]::
7989::$$$message_0077_0009_0002$$$::Another person was offered all of the available water to extinguish their raw, parched throat, while others in the same situation died.[lr]::
7990::$$$message_0077_0009_0003$$$::Someone here tried to flee the fire as fast as they could, but the people left behind died.::
7991::$$$message_0077_0010_0000$$$::And...[lr]::
7992::$$$message_0077_0010_0001$$$::Someone died here because they gave whatever it was that kept them alive to someone they didn't even know.::
7993::$$$message_0077_0011_0000$$$::[font italic=true]...[font italic=false][lr]::
7994::$$$message_0077_0011_0001$$$::I don't like thinking about that.[lr]::
7995::$$$message_0077_0011_0002$$$::Just thinking about people trying to help and becoming victims for their trouble makes me angry.[lr]::
7996::$$$message_0077_0011_0003$$$::Is it too much to ask for everyone to be saved, and for them to get their happy ending afterward?[lr]::
7997::$$$message_0077_0011_0004$$$::All I want is to see people peacefully prevail. Why can't that happen?::
7998::$$$message_0077_0012_0000$$$::[font italic=true]"That's a tough one. What you're essentially saying is that you want to save everyone."[font italic=false]::
7999::$$$message_0077_0013_0000$$$::That was Kiritsugu's response to the question when a very young me asked it.[lr]::
8000::$$$message_0077_0013_0001$$$::As a child, I obviously refused to accept that idea.[lr]::
8001::$$$message_0077_0013_0002$$$::"But you saved me, Kiritsugu. I knew you were a magician, and you could do anything.[lr]::
8002::$$$message_0077_0013_0003$$$::I knew you were a champion of justice who wouldn't let anyone suffer, and you did it without asking for any reward.[lr]::
8003::$$$message_0077_0013_0004$$$::That's why I've always believed you managed to save everyone back then."::
8004::$$$message_0077_0014_0000$$$::In response to me shouting this at him, Kiritsugu looked more troubled than I'd ever seen him, and said something I remember to this day.::
8005::$$$message_0077_0015_0000$$$::[font italic=true]"Shirou. Saving one person means you don't save someone else. Listen. Being saved by a champion of justice only means you're one of the few they managed to reach. It might be obvious, but that's what a champion of justice is."[font italic=false]::
8006::$$$message_0077_0016_0000$$$::Yeah, I get that.[lr]::
8007::$$$message_0077_0016_0001$$$::And now that it's been pointed out, it seems so obvious.[lr]::
8008::$$$message_0077_0016_0002$$$::Imagine if there was a burglar and some hostages, and the burglar intends to kill the hostages.[lr]::
8009::$$$message_0077_0016_0003$$$::Under normal circumstances, a majority of the hostages would probably die.::
8010::$$$message_0077_0017_0000$$$::But if by some miracle all the hostages were saved, there's [font italic=true]someone[font italic=false] who didn't get saved.[lr]::
8011::$$$message_0077_0017_0001$$$::The burglar, of course, since saving the hostages was done at the cost of his life.[lr]::
8012::$$$message_0077_0017_0002$$$::The people the champion of justice saves are only those whom the champion of justice deems to save.[lr]::
8013::$$$message_0077_0017_0003$$$::That's why saving [font italic=true]everyone[font italic=false] is impossible... Even God can't do that.::
8014::$$$message_0077_0018_0000$$$::"Especially if it's a natural disaster. No person is able to save everyone and everything."[lr]::
8015::$$$message_0077_0018_0001$$$::The fire ten years ago was like that.[lr]::
8016::$$$message_0077_0018_0002$$$::As someone who was miraculously saved from the incident, it wasn't my place to say anything at this point.::
8017::$$$message_0077_0019_0000$$$::"But I still don't like it."[lr]::
8018::$$$message_0077_0019_0001$$$::I don't want anything like that.[lr]::
8019::$$$message_0077_0019_0002$$$::I don't like the idea that there's a limitation to who can be saved.[lr]::
8020::$$$message_0077_0019_0003$$$::No matter how impossible it may be, I need to reach out to help.[lr]::
8021::$$$message_0077_0019_0004$$$::I can't stand to see people around me die, like back then.::
8022::$$$message_0077_0020_0000$$$::If the person I am now had been there ten years ago, I would've thrown myself into the fire[line2][lr]::
8023::$$$message_0077_0020_0001$$$::"But then I would've died, and for nothing."[lr]::
8024::$$$message_0077_0020_0002$$$::That would've happened for sure.[lr]::
8025::$$$message_0077_0020_0003$$$::Geez, I can't even fantasize in my head.::
8026::$$$message_0077_0021_0000$$$::"Oh crap. I can't believe it's already five."[lr]::
8027::$$$message_0077_0021_0001$$$::A bell in the distance rings, chiming five o'clock.[lr]::
8028::$$$message_0077_0021_0002$$$::I get up from the bench, and hurry to my part-time job.::
8029::$$$message_0077_0022_0000$$$::By the time I'm done working, the sun has long since set.[lr]::
8030::$$$message_0077_0022_0001$$$::It's a little before eight o'clock.[lr]::
8031::$$$message_0077_0022_0002$$$::I finished about ten minutes earlier because I kind of overworked myself.[lr]::
8032::$$$message_0077_0022_0003$$$::Maybe it's because I stopped by that park before work. That might've motivated me to push myself harder.::
8033::$$$message_0077_0023_0000$$$::At the train station, the night is just getting started.[lr]::
8034::$$$message_0077_0023_0001$$$::There are a bunch of people milling about, and an endless stream of cars on the road.::
8035::$$$message_0077_0024_0000$$$::"Guess there's no need for me to get something for Fuji-nee."[lr]::
8036::$$$message_0077_0024_0001$$$::I walk along the path as I gaze up at a lighted building.[lr]::
8037::$$$message_0077_0024_0002$$$::It's the biggest building in Shinto, so I can't see all the way to the top.[lr]::
8038::$$$message_0077_0024_0003$$$::As I gaze at the building, enjoying the nighttime scenery...[lr]::
8039::$$$message_0077_0024_0004$$$::"Huh?"[lr]::
8040::$$$message_0077_0024_0005$$$::I think I see something bizarre.::
8041::$$$message_0077_0025_0000$$$::"What is that?"[lr]::
8042::$$$message_0077_0025_0001$$$::I stop and try to look to the very top.[lr]::
8043::$$$message_0077_0025_0002$$$::I squint, trying to bring what I see into focus, but it's like staring at grains of rice.::
8044::$$$message_0077_0026_0000$$$::"..."[lr]::
8045::$$$message_0077_0026_0001$$$::It looks like someone I know.::
8046::$$$message_0077_0027_0000$$$::But I can't think why this girl I know would have a reason to be there.[lr]::
8047::$$$message_0077_0027_0001$$$::It doesn't seem like she's going to do anything up there.[lr]::
8048::$$$message_0077_0027_0002$$$::But she's just standing there, looking down at the city, as the wind ruffles her hair.::
8049::$$$message_0077_0028_0000$$$::[font italic=true]...[font italic=false][lr]::
8050::$$$message_0077_0028_0001$$$::She doesn't seem to notice me down below.[lr]::
8051::$$$message_0077_0028_0002$$$::Actually, there's no way she could see me.[lr]::
8052::$$$message_0077_0028_0003$$$::Even my near perfect vision, enhanced with magecraft, can barely distinguish what's up there.[lr]::
8053::$$$message_0077_0028_0004$$$::I'm able to tell she's up there because she's isolated, but there's no way she would be able to pick me out of a crowd on the ground.::
8054::$$$message_0077_0029_0000$$$::She's just looking down at the town.[lr]::
8055::$$$message_0077_0029_0001$$$::It seems like she's looking for something; I can almost feel her sharp gaze even at this distance.[lr]::
8056::$$$message_0077_0029_0002$$$::[font italic=true]...[font italic=false][lr]::
8057::$$$message_0077_0029_0003$$$::I forget how long it's been, but I continue to look up at the girl standing in the void.[lr]::
8058::$$$message_0077_0029_0004$$$::She stands at the top of a high tower.[lr]::
8059::$$$message_0077_0029_0005$$$::She's like a magician, looking down at the surface world with the bright moon shining bright behind her.::
8060::$$$message_0077_0030_0000$$$::"Oh."[lr]::
8061::$$$message_0077_0030_0001$$$::And then...[lr]::
8062::$$$message_0077_0030_0002$$$::She disappears, apparently done with whatever brought her up there.[lr]::
8063::$$$message_0077_0030_0003$$$::The rooftop stands empty, and the scenery returns back to nothing more than the beautiful night sky.[lr]::
8064::$$$message_0077_0030_0004$$$::"Was that Tohsaka up there?"::
8065::$$$message_0077_0031_0000$$$::I can't be sure, but I'm probably right about who it was, at least.[lr]::
8066::$$$message_0077_0031_0001$$$::There aren't many girls I know who stand out like her, and besides, I'm not so out of it I'd fail to notice a girl I secretly admire.::
8067::$$$message_0077_0032_0000$$$::"Huh. Er..."[lr]::
8068::$$$message_0077_0032_0001$$$::It's just...[lr]::
8069::$$$message_0077_0032_0002$$$::Tohsaka sure has a weird way of spending her time.::

